  "prompt": "Is six hours of sleep enough for a 10-year-old?",
  "response": "For a 10-year-old, six hours of sleep is generally not enough. The American Academy of Sleep Medicine recommends that children aged 6 to 12 years should get 9 to 12 hours of sleep per night for optimal health and well-being. \n\nGetting enough sleep is crucial for a child's growth, development, and performance in school. Consistently sleeping less than the recommended amount can lead to issues such as difficulty concentrating, mood swings, and even health problems over time.\n\nIf you're concerned about your child's sleep, it might be helpful to establish a consistent bedtime routine and create a sleep-friendly environment to ensure they get the rest they need. If sleep issues persist, consulting with a pediatrician could be beneficial.",
